                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>F</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>g</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>F</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>N</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>100</m:mn>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>980</m:mn>
                      <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="normal">N</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">F</m:mi>
                        <m:mi mathvariant="normal">N</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>F</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>N</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>980</m:mn>
                      <m:mspace width="0.166667em"/>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="normal">N</m:mi>
                      <m:mspace width="4pt"/>
                      <m:mi> upwards </m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
              </m:mtable>
            </m:math>
          </equation>
          </item> <item> <label> Quote the final answer </label>
          <para id="id72842">The normal force is 980 N upwards. It exactly balances the gravitational force downwards so there is no net force and no acceleration on the man. The reading on the scale is 980 N. </para>
          </item> </list> </solution>
</exercise>
          <para id="id72860">In the previous two examples we got exactly the same result because the net acceleration on the man was zero! If the lift is accelerating downwards things are slightly different and now we will get a more interesting answer!</para>
<exercise id="secfhsst_id3195"><title> Normal Forces 3 </title>
