                        <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mi>N</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                    <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>μ</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>32</m:mn>
                        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>μ</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  </m:mtd>
                  <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                      <m:mo>,</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>25</m:mn>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
              </m:mtable>
            </m:math>
          </equation>
          <para id="id75177">Note that the coefficient of friction does not have a unit as it shows a ratio. The value for the coefficient of friction friction can have any value up to a maximum of 0,25. When a force less than 8 N is applied, the coefficient of friction will be less than 0,25.</para>
          </item> <item> <label> Find the coefficient of kinetic friction </label>
          <para id="id75192">The coefficient of kinetic friction is sometimes also called the coefficient of dynamic friction. Here we look at when the block is moving:</para>
