            <item id="uid300">the radius of the planet Zirgon (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:msub></m:math>) in terms of the radius of the Earth (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:msub></m:math>), <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mi>E</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math></item>
          </list>
          </item> <item> <label> Determine how to approach the problem </label>
          <para id="id79400">We are required to determine the man's weight on Zirgon (<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mi>Z</m:mi></m:msub></m:math>). We can do this by using:</para>
