        <para id="id88108">Similarly, 36 km<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>hr<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>= 10 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>.</para>
        </item> <item> <label> Choose a frame of reference </label>
        <para id="id88168">Let us choose the direction from the batsman to the bowler as the positive direction. Then the initial velocity of the ball is <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mi>i</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> = -15 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>, while the final velocity of the ball is <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mi>f</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> = 10 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>.</para>
