<exercise id="secfhsst_id9345"><title> Conservation of Momentum 2 </title>
        <problem id="probfhsst_id9346">
        <para id="id91264">A helicopter flies at a speed of 275 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>. The pilot fires a missile forward out of a gun barrel at a speed of 700 m<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mo>·</m:mo></m:math>s<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:math>. The respective masses of the helicopter and the missile are 5000 kg and 50 kg. Calculate the new speed of the helicopter immmediately after the missile had been fired. </para>
        </problem>
